Raw Job Description:
The Global Energy Infrastructure Solutions (GEIS) group is part of the wider Eaton Electrical Group and contains the Crouse Hinds division which manufactures high grade electrical products for hazardous, industrial, and commercial applications world-wide. We are looking for a Supply Chain Analyst to ensure the timely supply of products within GEIS portfolio. The successful candidate will work with product managers and suppliers to achieve inventory and customer service goals.

We are an engineering-to-order-come business, and if you are looking to get stuck into a complex challenge that not only allows you but actively encourages you to look at better ways of working, this could be your role.

Key Duties

- Manage the inbound supply of materials for a nominated portfolio.
- Create, review, and execute purchasing plans within budgets and targets.
- Review open POs for potential changes and also new PO recommendations that will keep the plan moving.
- Build and maintain stakeholder relationships with focus on accurate communication.
- Analyse purchasing processes to eliminate negative impacts through continuous improvement.
- Implement the most efficient cost-to-serve model using existing organisational knowledge.
- Working with the Supply Chain and Logistics teams to optimise stock flow, resolving capacity, costs, and availability conflicts.
- Manage vendor communication and negotiation to ensure alignment on delivery schedules, pricing, and service expectations.

Qualifications

- Minimum of 2 years of experience as a supply chain or logistics analysts preferably for a manufacturing firm in any industry (for e.g. electrical, mechanical, healthcare, FMCG).
- Knowledge of supply chain concepts, including how safety stock levels can be influenced.
- Intermediate Excel skills with experience in SAP. 
- Tertiary qualifications in supply chain, business, or engineering.
- Self-motivated, team player, willing to learn, problem solver.

What We Offer

- Competitive salary with access to bonus scheme
- Inclusive working environment
- Volunteer days
- Outstanding training and development programs for both professional and personal development

About Lyka:Lyka was founded in 2018 by Anna Podolsky, inspired by her dog, Lyka, who was suffering from chronic health issues despite being on "premium" kibble. Together with Gabriel Guedes (COO) and Dr. Matthew Muir (Integrative Veterinarian), they built Lyka from the ground up with one core belief: better food can radically improve a pet's healthspan and quality of life.

Lyka's meals are vet-formulated and gently cooked from real food ingredients. Delivered via a flexible subscription model, Lyka meals have driven remarkable improvements for tens of thousands of customers, supporting gut health, reducing intolerances, improving energy and mobility, and even promoting hair growth.

What began as home-cooked meals has since scaled into one of Australia's fastest-growing consumer companies, a vertically integrated, tech-enabled brand that is transforming pet health nationwide.

Lyka now operates from two offices, Sydney (HQ) and Melbourne, with three state-of-the-art food production facilities (two in Sydney, one in Melbourne) and a growing national footprint.

At Lyka, we're not just selling pet food—we're pioneering a new standard of wellness for pets. With strong product-market fit, deep customer love, and a track record of rapid growth, we're now entering our most ambitious chapter yet: building a generational brand and category-defining business with global impact.

The opportunity:As a Junior FP&A Analyst, you'll be part of the team that turns numbers into real business insight. One day you'll be working on gross margin models, helping the Manufacturing & Supply Chain team understand performance, and the next you'll be digging into data from our NSAW platform, learning how to spot trends and prepare reports that actually matter.

You won't just be crunching numbers in isolation — you'll be part of budgeting cycles, pulling everything together behind the scenes, checking accuracy, and making sure leaders have the clarity they need. You'll also get hands-on with tools like Planful, supporting stakeholders, troubleshooting issues, and building confidence in how financial systems work.

What makes this role exciting is the variety. You'll be jumping in on analytical projects, preparing datasets, creating first-cut reports, and building the kind of analysis that influences decisions across the business. On top of that, you'll have the chance to support process improvements — testing ideas, documenting changes, and spotting ways to make reporting faster and smarter.

And every month, you'll help shape the story of the business by contributing to the budget vs actuals reporting, pulling results together and drafting analysis that helps the team see the bigger picture.

Requirements

We're looking for someone who's curious about the numbers and eager to learn. Maybe you've studied Finance, Accounting, Economics, Data Analytics, or something similar, or you've already had some exposure to FP&A, financial analysis, or business/data analysis through work, internships, or uni projects. If you're in the early stages of your career and keen to grow, this could be the perfect next step.

You'll need to be comfortable in Excel, pivot tables, lookups, and the basics of financial modelling. If you've worked with large datasets before or dabbled in tools like Power BI, Tableau, Looker, or SQL, that's a bonus. Don't worry if you haven't, though. We value willingness to learn just as much as experience. Any exposure to ERP or budgeting tools (Planful, SAP, NetSuite, etc.) is a nice-to-have, but not a dealbreaker.

What matters most is how you approach the work. You've got an analytical mindset, an eye for detail, and you're not afraid to ask questions to really understand what's going on. You enjoy working with others, can explain your findings clearly, and you're adaptable enough to handle the pace of a growing business. Most importantly, you bring a proactive, growth mindset — ready to pick up new technical skills, expand your financial knowledge, and support the team along the way.

Benefits

- Work in a fast-growing start-up, experiencing what goes behind the scenes to sustain hyper-growth for a start-up with a physical product! 
- Growth and Development - Lyka is growing extremely quickly, which means you will have the opportunity to experience different challenges every day and progressively acquire more responsibilities as our facility and team expand. We provide an annual L&D budget for you to continue your personal development.  
- Work for a sustainability-focused company - we care about the health of our dogs and our planet. We're proud to be Australia's only carbon-negative and plastic-negative pet wellness company and we're always looking at ways for us to improve sustainability practices.  
- Be part of a diverse top-talent team, coming from widely different backgrounds and geographies.  
- Up to 18 weeks of paid parental leave top-up 
- Wellbeing assistance and tools to take care of your mental and physical wellbeing so you can do your best work 
- Pupper parent support to care for your furry friends - flexible arrangements for new pets, pet-friendly offices, discounts, and financial allowance for dog training and care to help them live their best life!

We celebrate diversity, are devoted to creating an inclusive environment for all staff and encourage people of all backgrounds to apply. If you have any support or access requirements, we encourage you to advise us at the time of application.

Cognizant (NASDAQ: CTSH) is a leading provider of information technology, consulting, and business process services, dedicated to helping the world's leading companies build stronger businesses. Headquartered in Teaneck, New Jersey (U.S.), Cognizant combines a passion for client satisfaction, technology innovation, deep industry and business process expertise, and a global, collaborative workforce that embodies the future of work. Cognizant is a member of the NASDAQ-100, the S&P 500, the Forbes Global 2000, and the Fortune 500 and is ranked among the top performing and fastest growing companies in the world.

Our Culture

Your passion, integrity and experience are integral to Cognizant's success. You will join into a dynamic and expanding global leader in IT and Business consultancy where you will be valued for who you are. We take pride in our partnership with our clients, so your ability to add value and provide exceptional service to our clients is fundamental to your success. In return, you will be presented with opportunities to develop your career and collaborate with talented colleagues in a supportive, diverse environment.

At Cognizant we recognize that companies that are open and welcoming to a multi-culturally diverse workforce will thrive with fresh perspectives and collaborative knowledge. Cognizant focuses on promoting & increasing gender diversity and providing a workplace which encourages great participation and an equal playing field, where merit and accomplishment are the only criteria for success.

Position Summary

The Robotic Process Automation (RPA) Business Process Analyst will excel in RPA (Power automate), presenting both consulting and development skillsets. They will work closely with business stakeholders through completing consulting led RPA process assessments, documenting business processes, communicating to development teams on requirements and having experience in agile RPA delivery. They will collaborate with a client to enable them to deliver and scale RPA solutions. They will play a critical role in the growth of the Cognizant team and its RPA capability across ANZ. One key part of the role will be to identify quality and prioritising opportunities to automate process, demonstrating to clients the achievement of benefits and suggesting process improvements as part of a continuous journey.

Roles And Responsibilities

- RPA Tool understanding. (Uipath, Power Automate desktop, Blue Prism)
- Collaborating with stakeholders to understand “as-is” process, issues, areas for improvement, leveraging system data to confirm conclusions where necessary.
- Document business processes using Process Definition Documents (PDD), Standard Operating Procedures.
- Responsible for documenting business process flow charts using BPMN principles.
- Design clear and understandable “to=be” processes, replay them to the business and get sign off for them to be developed and implemented.
- Work with change management teams to ensure the early adoption of new processes.
- Working on Support and Maintenance activities
- Experience managing daily stand ups, retrospectives leveraging agile methodologies (Scrum).
- Project management: disciplined in managing project scope, timeline, and budget to meet deadlines.
- Work within project schedule constraints, communicating any identified project risks and issues.
- Create Handover Documentation
- Write test cases against the desired requirements.
- Review UAT test plans, run UAT triage and clarification/manage defects.
- Test and confirm the desired requirement has been met considering original ROI.

Mandatory Skills

- Strong analytical and strategic thinking.
- A proactive approach to identifying opportunities and driving solutions independently. 
- Able to understand complex processes and simplify where possible, or break down into sub-processes, ability to identify redundancy.
- Able to determine ROI of processes and create business pipeline. Work with the business to identify best cases for automation.
- Possess expert communication and facilitation.
- Working effectively with people at all levels of the organization to understand needs and deploy solutions. 
- Familiarity with digital tools and the ability to use statistical models and data to simulate and predict the impact of changes. 
- Thoroughness and a focus on detail are important for creating accurate and effective architectural designs. 
- The ability to navigate organizational politics and build consensus among different stakeholders. 
- Capable of playing a lead role and communicating requirements to both onshore and offshore teams.
- Ability to playback future “to-be” solutions to multiple audiences with varying degrees of technological maturity.
- Familiarisation with JIRA, Confluence tools
- Familiarity with Microsoft power automate.
- Possess excellent communication skills.
- Enthusiastic and unprompted attitude for implementing and developing fresh solutions.
- Knowledge of BPM, RPA, and AI API’s
- Initiative-taker: self-directed and initiative-taking in managing tasks and setting challenging targets to achieve client’s demands.

Next Steps

If you feel this opportunity suits you, or Cognizant is the type of organization you would like to join, we want to have a conversation with you! Please apply directly with us.

For a complete list of open opportunities with Cognizant, visit http://www.cognizant.com/careers. Cognizant is committed to providing Equal Employment Opportunities. Successful candidates will be required to undergo a background check.

Job Description

About the role:

You’ll collaborate with project teams, business analysts and engineers to understand and document business requirements. Your role will collaborate with the People First Bank business areas to assist with the deployment of Power BI within the organisation.

This role is offered as a 12 months fixed term contract with potential extension or permanency.

Key Responsibilities

-  Work with stakeholders to elicit, analyse, communicate and validate analytics and reporting requirements for Power BI. 
-  Facilitate workshops with business analysts to document business processes and requirements. 
-  Develop functional specifications for engineers. 
-  Assist in the development of Power BI semantic layer. 
-  Support the development and testing phases of data projects. 
-  Guide the business through the adoption of Power BI best practices. 
-  Design, build and development dashboards to meet business needs / requirements, ensuring that business needs are met. 

About You

You are outcomes focussed, have a curious mind-set and work collaboratively with the team and the business to support Power BI rollout.

What You Will Be Doing·        Becoming the face of ACY’s market analysis across multiple channels, including written, video, webinars, and social media.·        Building trust and authority with traders by delivering actionable insights and clear, engaging education.·        Using our professional studio and support team to create world-class market content that elevates your personal brand.·        Partnering with our marketing and sales teams to ensure your analysis drives new account growth and inspires existing traders.·        Continuously improving your craft by exploring new strategies, testing trading systems, and sharing insights with our client base.
This is a One-of-a-Kind Opportunity for You If You…·        Have a genuine passion for the global markets and love teaching traders how to succeed.·        Want to grow your visibility and become a recognised commentator in the trading industry.·        Enjoy creating content in different formats: writing, video, live webinars, and social media.·        Are confident on camera and thrive in front of a live audience.·        Have experience with MT4/MT5, Expert Advisors, and backtesting trading systems (a strong advantage).·        Are hungry to build your personal brand with the full backing of a global broker.
What We Require for This Role·        Minimum 3 years of experience in financial derivative trading or market commentary.·        Excellent written and spoken English with the ability to simplify complex financial topics.·        Confident communicator on video, webinars, and live events.·        Familiarity with online social media channels and content distribution.·        Bachelor’s degree in Finance, Economics, Business, or a related field preferred.·        Experience with Expert Advisors and backtesting on MT4/MT5 is highly valued.
Perks And Benefits: ·        A platform to grow your personal brand and gain media exposure across TV, press, and online.·        Access to our professional ‘mini Channel 7’ studio and content team.·        Support from industry veterans and global teams who will mentor and guide your career growth.·        Be part of a global broker with a 13+ year track record and clients in over 150 countries.·        Competitive salary with opportunities for growth into senior analyst or commentator roles.

Overview

The Graduate Research Analyst is a pivotal role within Canstar’s Research Department, tailored for graduates eager to delve into the financial services industry. Reporting to the Ratings Manager, this role focuses on contributing to the development and delivery of Canstar’s renowned star ratings and industry awards. This position requires strong analytical skills, adaptability, and collaboration, offering a solid foundation for building knowledge in financial products, market analytics, and consumer trends.

Key Responsibilities

Star Ratings and Awards Management

- Assist in the design and implementation of Canstar’s Star Ratings and Awards, applying robust methodologies and maintaining consistency with industry standards.

- Participate in research projects on behalf of financial institutions, government departments, and other related organisations.

General Duties

- Develop and maintain an understanding of consumer behaviour, product features, pricing trends, and regulatory issues such as disclosure and competition.
- Document procedures and maintain resources to support recurring and ad hoc research requests.

- Contribute to cross-functional projects by supplying analysis, insights, and solutions to other teams across the business.

Communication

- Liaise with both technical and non-technical stakeholders, translating complex concepts into clear, actionable insights.
- Collaborate with Editorial, Media, Product, and other teams to ensure alignment and effective communication of research outcomes.
- Participate in internal discussions and presentations relating to methodology, market trends, and award results.

Other Duties

- Remain open to taking on additional responsibilities or adapting to changes in job requirements.
- Engage in ongoing professional development and learning opportunities in the finance and research sectors.

Requirements

- Conduct real-time monitoring of security alerts and incidents utilising our SIEM tools (FortiSIEM and MS Sentinel) to ensure swift identification and resolution of potential threats.

- Conduct security awareness training sessions for customers to foster a security-conscious culture.

- Collaborate with all stakeholders to configure and fine-tune security tools, including EDR solutions, application control, firewalls, intrusion detection systems, and anti-malware software.

- Stay up-to-date with the latest cyber security trends, technologies, and best practices to continuously enhance our security posture.

- Experience with any SIEM products, ideally FortiSIEM and/or Microsoft Sentinel.

- Knowledge of network protocols, security architectures, and information security frameworks. 
- Ideally experience in conducting vulnerability assessments and remediation 
- Excellent analytical and problem-solving skills, with the ability to think critically and respond quickly to security incidents. 
- Effective communication and teamwork skills, with the ability to convey complex technical concepts to non-technical stakeholders. 
- Ideally experience in conducting vulnerability assessments and remediation using products such as Tenable and Microsoft Defender. 
- Working with user Cybersecurity Awareness training software such as uSecure or Microsoft based training modules.

We provide bold and impactful solutions delivering growth, certainty, and value. There is strength in difference. And we are different.

Job Description

As part of KordaMentha’s Major Projects Advisory team, we provide commercial, financial, transaction management, and strategic advice to government and private sector clients and we are seeking an Associate or Manager who is eager to lead and contribute to the growth of our team. 

In KordaMentha we are proud to be involved in all major infrastructure sectors including transport, energy, social infrastructure (health, housing, education, justice, and community infrastructure), real estate, defence and national security, and water. We are also currently involved in initiatives for the upcoming Olympic Games. 

Our team understands the challenges in delivering projects across the project lifecycle, and we thrive on this complexity. We are a market leader, and we are advising on some of Australia’s most significant infrastructure projects. 

Your opportunity 

Due to continued growth, we have opportunities for talented individuals, early in their careers, to join our Major Projects Advisory Team in Queensland.  

You will play a key role in working in a growth team to provide financial and commercial advice on major infrastructure projects across every stage of the asset lifecycle, from investment decision and business case, through procurement and transaction processes, throughout the delivery phase and into operations. As an Associate you will be responsible for developing deliverables and leading initiatives on projects across various functions and work streams.  

You will bring skills and experience, preferably from major infrastructure backgrounds, across: 

- work closely with key government and private sector clients to plan, assess and deliver significant projects and programs;
- interact directly with clients and key stakeholders;
- develop and apply your management skills to help clients navigate through complex environments;
- assist the team in the development of quantitative and qualitative analysis;
- prepare and deliver high-quality written reports, presentations and client deliverables;
- be part of a collaborative team environment in identifying key issues/risks and developing mitigation strategies and solutions, and provide industry leading advice;
- stay abreast of industry trends and emerging practices to adapt strategies accordingly;
- work alongside a team that acts with integrity and prioritises the wellbeing of their people; and
- participate in business development, marketing activities and attend industry events.
- Building financial models and conducting financial analysis. 

Qualifications

- Tertiary qualifications in commerce, finance, economics, law, engineering, or a similar discipline. 
- Relevant and demonstrated experience in the private sector or government (for example, professional services firms, management consultancy, corporate advisory, government infrastructure delivery teams, government treasury departments, investment banking or infrastructure funds).  
- Commercial expertise in a similar role working on large infrastructure projects ideally from a consultant/advisory perspective. 
- Highly developed written and oral communication skills.  
- A passion for doing work that matters and thriving on the challenge of solving complex problems, juggling competing demands, and working as part of a team in delivering solutions in a dynamic, fast-paced environment.

Join KordaMentha — Where Your Growth Is Our Priority 

We don’t just hire talent; we invest in it - with support that accelerates your success in every way 

Why Join Us? 

- Professional Development: Expert mentorship, tailored training via KordaMentha Business School, study support, and our Accelerate program for Analysts to Associate Directors — build your brand, expand your network, and gain strategic insights from senior leaders 

- Flexibility: We champion work/life integration with options that fit your lifestyle. 

- Career Growth: Merit-based promotions, secondments, and opportunities to work alongside senior leaders on impactful projects. 

- Leave That Works for You: Buy extra leave, swap public holidays, and access volunteer, generous parental leave and career break options. 

- Culture & Connection: Social events, cultural celebrations, and our bi-annual black-tie ball. 

- Family Support: Flexible parental leave, return-to-work support through our partner GracePapers, and resources for every stage of family life. 

- Health & Wellbeing: Inclusive wellness initiatives and confidential and industry leading EAP for you and your family. 

This isn’t just a job — it’s a place where your ambitions are nurtured, your wellbeing is valued, and your contributions celebrated. Ready to shape your future with us? 

Additional Information

At KordaMentha, we believe there is strength in difference. Our entrepreneurial spirit expands the possibilities for action. We approach situations, challenges, and opportunities with optimism, curiosity, and diversity of thought. We seek novel solutions to problems and encourage unconventional and innovative approaches. 

Our team's diverse skillsets, backgrounds and experiences fuel KordaMentha's different mindset. We encourage candidates from all backgrounds to apply, recognising that talent and potential extend beyond traditional qualifications. Our selection process values diverse perspectives and considers each applicant's unique strengths and capabilities.

- Collaborate with a supportive, forward-thinking team that thrives on innovation.
- Expand your technical skillset while helping shape the future of data-driven decision-making.

Our people are customer obsessed. They prioritise the needs and satisfaction of the customer above all else.  Our mindset fosters innovation and creates strong, lasting customer relationships as we strive to be the most customer centric company in Australia and New Zealand.

As a Data Analyst, you’ll work closely with the Home Ownership Data Analytics team, who are doubling down on delivering exceptional customer and product outcomes.

Each day, you’ll go above and beyond to: 

- Design, prototype, visualise, test, and deploy end-to-end analytics solutions based on business needs.
- Deliver insights that create tangible value for our business partners and customers.
- Implement and validate minor changes to ensure data accuracy and integrity.
- Maintain and support data models, SQL ETLs, and Power BI dashboards.
- Partner with NAB’s Home Ownership business to drive platform excellence and customer success.

We’re looking for the best and brightest to deliver the best for our customers. You’ll need: 

- Demonstrated experience as a Data Analyst in complex business environments.
- Proficiency in data visualisation tools such as Power BI or Tableau.
- Strong SQL skills and experience working with data marts or cloud-based data platforms.
- Ability to analyse and present data in a clear, meaningful way.
- Strong communication skills, with the ability to explain complex concepts in a simple way. Proactivity, curiosity, and eagerness to learn.
- A degree in Business, Data Analytics, Computer Science, Statistics, Information Systems, or a related field.

A diverse and inclusive workplace works better for everyone

We are committed to providing an environment where you can work your way.

A Little About Us.

From Helensburgh in the north to North Durras in the south, ISLHD covers an area of 5,687 square kms. That’s 5,687 square kms of beautiful beaches, coastal cycling tracks, lush rainforests, incredible bushwalks and friendly people. The region is also host to many annual food, wine and arts festivals and events.

Located on Dharawal and Yuin Country, ISLHD operate seven hospital sites, employ over 8,500 staff and provide community health services across 58 locations. Commute times are short, childcare and schooling options are plentiful, and Sydney and Canberra are close by.

Benefits Of Working With ISLHD.

We understand that balancing career aspirations with the demand of the everyday, as well as maintaining a healthy work-life balance, can be a challenge. To help with this, we offer a range of benefits which include:

-  Allocated Days Off (ADO) - once a month take a paid day off (eligible full-time employees)
-  Salary packaging - less tax and more take-home pay
-  Novated leasing - lease a car and pay for all running costs out of your pre-taxed salary (eligible full-time employees)
-  Fitness Passport - discounted gym membership that both you and your family can enjoy (eligible employees)
-  Employee Assistance Program (EAP) - free confidential and professional assistance for staff and their families
- Career progression, professional development and secondment opportunities

Requirements

Apply now by reading the Position Description, then, using our online portal, submit a resume and answer the selection criteria within the application. In addition, please note you must have the following essential requirements:

- Applicable vaccination requirements for a Category B role.

This is a temporary leave relief position until 31 December 2026 with the possibility of extension at same or reduced hours, job share to be considered for this role.

ISLHD is an equal opportunity employer. We celebrate diversity and are committed to creating an inclusive environment for all employees.

ISLHD is dedicated to fostering a child-safe environment that respects and upholds the rights of children and young people, aligned with NSW Health’s commitment to implementing the Child Safe Standards. We aim to ensure that children and young people feel safe, supported, and included in their care. All current and prospective staff are expected to prioritise the safety, welfare, and wellbeing of children and young people, actively working to protect them from harm and abuse.

Mercor connects elite creative and technical talent with leading AI research labs. Headquartered in San Francisco, our investors include Benchmark, General Catalyst, Peter Thiel, Adam D'Angelo, Larry Summers, and Jack Dorsey.

Role Overview

- Position: Hedge Fund Expert – Contract, Remote
- Commitment: At least 10 hours per week, Duration: Minimum four weeks
- Join a research project with a leading foundational model AI lab. Contribute your expertise in hedge funds to advance AI research.

Responsibilities

- Evaluate financial models and AI-generated content for accuracy and depth in hedge fund domains.
- Review market sizing, TAM analysis, and investment research to ensure alignment with domain-specific principles.
- Provide detailed feedback to AI research teams to improve the accuracy of model outputs in financial contexts.
- Develop evaluation rubrics to assess the quality of AI-generated financial tasks and solutions.
- Collaborate with other subject matter experts to ensure consistency and domain relevance in training data.
- Work independently and asynchronously to meet project deadlines and contribute to the continuous improvement of AI model performance.

Requirements / Qualifications

Must-Have Qualifications

- At least 2 years of experience in top hedge funds
- Experience in financial modeling, market sizing/TAM analysis, investment/analysis research, or earnings predictions and analysis

Preferred Qualifications

- Experience with AI model evaluation in financial domains
- Strong analytical and problem-solving skills

Engagement Details

- Compensation: $130/hour, with potential increases for top performers
- Schedule: Flexible, fully asynchronous
- Duration: Minimum four weeks, starting in October
- Contract Type: At-will contractor
- Location: Remote, based in U.S./UK/Canada/Europe/Australia

Application Process (Takes 20-30 mins to complete)

- Upload resume
- AI interview based on your resume
- Submit form

Resources & Support

About Your New Role…

As one of our full-time, permanent Quality Analysts based at our Richlands site, you would be responsible for both leading and supporting the technical analytical work on site (both Syrup Rooms and Lines).

The role will be worked on a 24/7 roster, with rotating alternate shifts to other Quality Analysts on site.

The role is not only integral to the success of our business, but also offers scope for accelerated career progression, dependant on you and your successes…on the work you love to do!

What will you be doing?

We are looking for someone who is both curious and passionate about both the technical and analytical aspects of our work – You can work both autonomously, as well as be able to collaborate when and where needed with your peers. You take QMS, HACCP and Food Safety Programmes seriously, and take pride in the responsibility of leadership in ensuring that these standards are followed and actioned.

A typical day would look like (but not be limited to):

A Little About Us.

From Helensburgh in the north to North Durras in the south, ISLHD covers an area of 5,687 square kms. That’s 5,687 square kms of beautiful beaches, coastal cycling tracks, lush rainforests, incredible bushwalks and friendly people. The region is also host to many annual food, wine and arts festivals and events.

Located on Dharawal and Yuin Country, ISLHD operate seven hospital sites, employ over 8,500 staff and provide community health services across 58 locations. Commute times are short, childcare and schooling options are plentiful, and Sydney and Canberra are close by.

Benefits Of Working With ISLHD.

We understand that balancing career aspirations with the demand of the everyday, as well as maintaining a healthy work-life balance, can be a challenge. To help with this, we offer a range of benefits which include:

-  Allocated Days Off (ADO) - once a month take a paid day off (eligible full-time employees)
-  Salary packaging - less tax and more take-home pay
-  Novated leasing - lease a car and pay for all running costs out of your pre-taxed salary (eligible full-time employees)

- Career progression, professional development and secondment opportunities

Responsibilities

Engagement Details

At Mindrift, innovation meets opportunity. We believe in using the power of collective human intelligence to ethically shape the future of AI.

The Mindrift platform, launched and powered by Toloka, connects domain experts with cutting-edge AI projects from innovative tech clients. Our mission is to unlock the potential of GenAI by tapping into real-world expertise from across the globe.

Who we're looking for:

We're looking for curious and intellectually proactive contributors, the kind of person who double-checks assumptions and plays devil's advocate.

Are you comfortable with ambiguity and complexity? Does an async, remote, flexible opportunity sound exciting? Would you like to learn how modern AI systems are tested and evaluated?

This is a flexible, project-based opportunity well-suited for:

- Analysts, researchers, or consultants with strong critical thinking skills
- Students (senior undergrads / grad students) looking for an intellectually interesting gig
- People open to a part-time and non-permanent opportunity

About the project:

We're on the hunt for QAs for autonomous AI agents for a new project focused on validating and improving complex task structures, policy logic, and agent evaluation frameworks. Throughout the project, you'll have to balance quality assurance, research, and logical problem-solving. This project opportunity is ideal for people who enjoy looking at systems holistically and thinking through scenarios, implications, and edge cases.

You do not need a coding background, but you must be curious, intellectually rigorous, and capable of evaluating the soundness and consistency of complex setups. If you've ever excelled in things like consulting, CHGK, Olympiads, case solving, or systems thinking — you might be a great fit.

What you'll be doing:

- Reviewing evaluation tasks and scenarios for logic, completeness, and realism
- Identifying inconsistencies, missing assumptions, or unclear decision points
- Helping define clear expected behaviors (gold standards) for AI agents
- Annotating cause-effect relationships, reasoning paths, and plausible alternatives
- Thinking through complex systems and policies as a human would to ensure agents are tested properly
- Working closely with QA, writers, or developers to suggest refinements or edge case coverage

How to get started:

Apply to this post, qualify, and get the chance to contribute to a project aligned with your skills, on your own schedule. Shape the future of AI while building tools that benefit everyone.

Requirements

- Excellent analytical thinking: Can reason about complex systems, scenarios, and logical implications
- Strong attention to detail: Can spot contradictions, ambiguities, and vague requirements
- Familiarity with structured data formats: Can read, not necessarily write JSON/YAML
- Can assess scenarios holistically: What's missing, what's unrealistic, what might break?
- Good communication and clear writing (in English) to document your findings. 

We also value applicants who have:

- Experience with policy evaluation, logic puzzles, case studies, or structured scenario design
- Background in consulting, academia, olympiads (e.g. logic/math/informatics), or research
- Exposure to LLMs, prompt engineering, or AI-generated content
- Familiarity with QA or test-case thinking (edge cases, failure modes, "what could go wrong")
- Some understanding of how scoring or evaluation works in agent testing (precision, coverage, etc.)

Benefits

- Get paid for your expertise, with rates that can go up to $38/hour depending on your skills, experience, and project needs
- Take part in a flexible, remote, freelance project that fits around your primary professional or academic commitments
- Participate in an advanced AI project and gain valuable experience to enhance your portfolio
- Influence how future AI models understand and communicate in your field of expertise

At Mindrift, innovation meets opportunity. We believe in using the power of collective human intelligence to ethically shape the future of AI.

The Mindrift platform, launched and powered by Toloka, connects domain experts with cutting-edge AI projects from innovative tech clients. Our mission is to unlock the potential of GenAI by tapping into real-world expertise from across the globe.

Who we're looking for:

We're looking for curious and intellectually proactive contributors, the kind of person who double-checks assumptions and plays devil's advocate.

Are you comfortable with ambiguity and complexity? Does an async, remote, flexible opportunity sound exciting? Would you like to learn how modern AI systems are tested and evaluated?

This is a flexible, project-based opportunity well-suited for:

- Analysts, researchers, or consultants with strong critical thinking skills
- Students (senior undergrads / grad students) looking for an intellectually interesting gig
- People open to a part-time and non-permanent opportunity

About the project:

We're on the hunt for QAs for autonomous AI agents for a new project focused on validating and improving complex task structures, policy logic, and agent evaluation frameworks. Throughout the project, you'll have to balance quality assurance, research, and logical problem-solving. This project opportunity is ideal for people who enjoy looking at systems holistically and thinking through scenarios, implications, and edge cases.

You do not need a coding background, but you must be curious, intellectually rigorous, and capable of evaluating the soundness and consistency of complex setups. If you've ever excelled in things like consulting, CHGK, Olympiads, case solving, or systems thinking — you might be a great fit.

What you'll be doing:

- Reviewing evaluation tasks and scenarios for logic, completeness, and realism
- Identifying inconsistencies, missing assumptions, or unclear decision points
- Helping define clear expected behaviors (gold standards) for AI agents
- Annotating cause-effect relationships, reasoning paths, and plausible alternatives
- Thinking through complex systems and policies as a human would to ensure agents are tested properly
- Working closely with QA, writers, or developers to suggest refinements or edge case coverage

How to get started:

Apply to this post, qualify, and get the chance to contribute to a project aligned with your skills, on your own schedule. Shape the future of AI while building tools that benefit everyone.

Requirements

- Excellent analytical thinking: Can reason about complex systems, scenarios, and logical implications
- Strong attention to detail: Can spot contradictions, ambiguities, and vague requirements
- Familiarity with structured data formats: Can read, not necessarily write JSON/YAML
- Can assess scenarios holistically: What's missing, what's unrealistic, what might break?
- Good communication and clear writing (in English) to document your findings. 

We also value applicants who have:

- Experience with policy evaluation, logic puzzles, case studies, or structured scenario design
- Background in consulting, academia, olympiads (e.g. logic/math/informatics), or research
- Exposure to LLMs, prompt engineering, or AI-generated content
- Familiarity with QA or test-case thinking (edge cases, failure modes, "what could go wrong")
- Some understanding of how scoring or evaluation works in agent testing (precision, coverage, etc.)

Benefits

- Get paid for your expertise, with rates that can go up to $38/hour depending on your skills, experience, and project needs
- Take part in a flexible, remote, freelance project that fits around your primary professional or academic commitments
- Participate in an advanced AI project and gain valuable experience to enhance your portfolio
- Influence how future AI models understand and communicate in your field of expertise

Introduction:

About Us

Adelaide Primary Health Network (Adelaide PHN) is an independent, not for profit, primary health care organisation based in Adelaide. We aim to improve the health and wellbeing of the Adelaide community by coordinating and integrating health and community services and by working in partnership to identify local needs and create strategies in response to keeping people well and out of hospital; improving their experience AND their health outcomes - to deliver on our vision of ‘shaping the health system to deliver better outcomes for vulnerable people, and a healthier Adelaide’.

Why you should come work with us

Adelaide PHN offers a great range of benefits to our employees, including:

- Competitive remuneration and work-life balance.
- Access to generous not for profit salary packaging benefits, including up to $15,900 for living expenses and $2,650 for meal and entertainment.
- Additional paid leave between Christmas and New Year, in addition to annual leave entitlements.

- Option to substitute public holidays.

Description:

This Data Analyst role will have a key focus on supporting the data and reporting needs at the Adelaide PHN by:

- Proactively monitoring for new and emerging data to provide insights to health and service needs in the Adelaide PHN region and inform organisational strategic, operational and regulatory performance.
- Acting as a subject matter expert within the organisation regarding data and analytics as appropriate e.g. population health, aged care, mental health, methods/data collection systems
- Providing analysis, interpretation, and reporting/presentation of data to inform of a range of planning and performance deliverables, including, but not limited to, the Adelaide PHN Needs Assessment, 12-month performance report and annual report.
- Participating in data management and data governance.

The role may also undertake other data collection, analysis, reporting and quality improvement initiatives to support the wider organisation.

This position is offered as a full-time, 12 month fixed-term contract. Future employment is subject to ongoing funding.

There is flexibility to work from home 1-2 days per week post induction and training.

For more information, you can view the position description here (SEEK, Indeed and LinkedIn applicants please go to our website).

Skills and Experiences:

To be successful in this role you’ll need:

- Tertiary qualifications in data analytics, epidemiology, public health, evaluation, biostatistics or similar discipline, and/or significant relevant work experience in these fields is required. 
- Demonstrated experience working in primary health care and/or public health sectors. 
- Knowledge of the Australian primary health care sector, social determinants of health and population health data.
- Demonstrated experience undertaking analysis and developing reports to provide insights on organisational strategic, operational and regulatory performance.
- Proven ability to implement and manage appropriate systems and processes to maintain the quality and integrity of information and data (quantitative and qualitative).
- Demonstrated knowledge in research methodological skills and capacity to interpret findings including statistical analysis.
- High level critical thinking and analytic skills with exceptional attention to detail and accuracy.
- Demonstrated highly competent computer skills and use of computer programs for data management and analysis, particularly Power BI and/or other reporting tools and business intelligence solutions.
- Demonstrated effective written and verbal communication skills, with a focus on facilitating and maintaining relationships. 
- Demonstrated ability to work autonomously and in teams, including across internal portfolios and external groups, in a collaborative environment.

You may have experience in previous roles in the primary or public health sector such as: Health Data Analyst, Business Intelligence Analyst or Officer, Health Research Analyst or Officer, Health Reporting Analyst, Population Health Analyst or Officer.

Throughout the project, you'll have to balance quality assurance, research, and logical problem-solving. This project opportunity is ideal for people who enjoy looking at systems holistically and thinking through scenarios, implications, and edge cases.

You do not need a coding background, but you must be curious, intellectually rigorous, and capable of evaluating the soundness and consistency of complex setups. If you've ever excelled in things like consulting, CHGK, Olympiads, case solving, or systems thinking — you might be a great fit.

What you'll be doing:

- Reviewing evaluation tasks and scenarios for logic, completeness, and realism
- Identifying inconsistencies, missing assumptions, or unclear decision points
- Helping define clear expected behaviors (gold standards) for AI agents
- Annotating cause-effect relationships, reasoning paths, and plausible alternatives
- Thinking through complex systems and policies as a human would to ensure agents are tested properly
- Working closely with QA, writers, or developers to suggest refinements or edge case coverage

How to get started:

Apply to this post, qualify, and get the chance to contribute to a project aligned with your skills, on your own schedule. Shape the future of AI while building tools that benefit everyone.

Requirements

- Excellent analytical thinking: Can reason about complex systems, scenarios, and logical implications
- Strong attention to detail: Can spot contradictions, ambiguities, and vague requirements
- Familiarity with structured data formats: Can read, not necessarily write JSON/YAML
- Can assess scenarios holistically: What's missing, what's unrealistic, what might break?
- Good communication and clear writing (in English) to document your findings. 

We also value applicants who have:

- Experience with policy evaluation, logic puzzles, case studies, or structured scenario design
- Background in consulting, academia, olympiads (e.g. logic/math/informatics), or research
- Exposure to LLMs, prompt engineering, or AI-generated content
- Familiarity with QA or test-case thinking (edge cases, failure modes, "what could go wrong")
- Some understanding of how scoring or evaluation works in agent testing (precision, coverage, etc.)

Benefits

- Get paid for your expertise, with rates that can go up to $38/hour depending on your skills, experience, and project needs
- Take part in a flexible, remote, freelance project that fits around your primary professional or academic commitments
- Participate in an advanced AI project and gain valuable experience to enhance your portfolio
- Influence how future AI models understand and communicate in your field of expertise

In this role, you'll:

Working within our Production Planning Lead Team at Sydney Trains, the primary purpose of our Production Planning Analyst role is to be accountable for developing, sustaining and continually improving the production planning processes, tools and practices required by the Maintenance Directorate to forecast and deliver current and future production calendars and data integrity.

About You

You will execute safety responsibilities, authorities and accountabilities consistent with Sydney Trains safety management system requirements.

You will facilitate the collection of maintenance scheduling requirements for various asset types and develop production planning rules and best practices to support an effective and efficient maintenance scheduling system.

You will take responsibility for the creation of maintenance schedule tasks for new equipment ensuring their compliance with the Technical Maintenance Plan (TMP) including the safety requirements and their alignment with the existing equipment.

This role will see you implement new/revised TMP across the network ensuring the maintenance schedule tasks are compliant with the standards and conduct risk analysis ensuring impact of the change is understood and risk is mitigated and communicated.

You will also contribute to the provisioning of maintenance services for future assets following capital projects ensuring the timely development of production plans.

You will also monitor the effectiveness of the plans and even distribution of the workload and lead continuous improvement of production plans, data integrity and production planning processes and tools.

You will utilise SAP (EAM) to manage maintenance data, scheduling tasks and reporting to support planning accuracy and compliance.

You shall work closely with stakeholders to ensure SAP data integrity, streamline scheduling workflows and implement improvements within the system.

Experience & Skills

Fund Size: €90M USD

Location: Bali, Indonesia (with global impact)

Additionally, you'll architect real-time analytics systems that can process streaming data and provide immediate insights, build AI-powered hypothesis testing frameworks that can validate or challenge business assumptions, and develop recommendation engines that can suggest optimal strategies based on data analysis.

Why It's Cool: Data is the new oil, and you're building the most advanced refineries to extract maximum value from information. This is detective work for the digital age, where you'll be developing technologies that can understand complex relationships in data and translate them into actionable intelligence. Your work will influence how organizations make critical decisions, and you'll be creating the foundation for a more data-driven world where insights drive better outcomes.

Bali Option: Uncover global data insights from your island base, where the clarity of tropical skies mirrors the clarity of insights you'll extract from complex datasets. About Us

Vinarchy. Redefining Wine.

Established in 2025 following the merger of Accolade Wines and Pernod Ricard Winemakers, Vinarchy is an exceptional global wine company committed to redefining wine, globally.

About The Role

We are excited to share an opportunity for the role of ESG Analyst to join Vinarchy’s Global Safety & Sustainability team. This is a full time, permanent position based in Adelaide and offering hybrid working.

The ESG Analyst will play a key role in supporting the global sustainability & climate strategy by managing data, analytics, and reporting across environmental, social, and governance (ESG) areas.

You’ll support the Global Sustainability & Climate Transition Manager in delivering robust ESG disclosures, tracking performance against targets (e.g. emissions, water, waste), and ensuring alignment with global frameworks such as TCFD, SBTi, GRI, and CSRD.

Communications skills will be key as you work closely with teams across global regions to provide insights that drive progress toward Vinarchy’s climate and sustainability goals.

Key Responsibilities

- Collect, validate, and manage ESG performance data across global operations, ensuring accuracy and audit readiness. 
- Support the implementation and optimisation of ESG data platforms and tools (e.g., Intelex). 
- Develop dashboards and visualisations to communicate sustainability performance effectively. 
- Assist in preparing ESG disclosures aligned with frameworks such as TCFD, GRI, SASB, CDP, and SBTi. 
- Contribute to Vinarchy’s annual Sustainability Report and other stakeholder publications. 
- Track global ESG reporting obligations and coordinate submissions to rating agencies and investor questionnaires. 
- Support ESG software rollout, user onboarding, training, and ongoing system improvements. 
- Analyse environmental metrics including Scope 1–3 emissions, energy, water, and waste, and support climate risk assessments. 
- Provide analytical support for sustainability initiatives such as renewable energy, biodiversity, and packaging. 
- Research ESG trends and best practices to drive continuous improvement and enhance internal capabilities. 

Other Requirements

- Occasional travel may be required to operational sites or regional offices 
- Role may expand as ESG frameworks and regulations evol

What We're Looking For

- Tertiary qualification in Environmental Science, Sustainability, Data Analytics, Finance, or a related discipline 
- 2–4 years' experience in ESG, sustainability analytics, corporate reporting, or data governance 
- Familiarity with key ESG reporting frameworks (e.g., GHG Protocol, CDP, GRI, TCFD) 
- Advanced Excel/data analysis skills, with proficiency in Power BI, Tableau, or similar tools 
- Strong attention to detail and organisational skills 

Why Join Us?

Vinarchy is a home for passionate people to do their very best work. We believe in empowering our people and celebrating success.

We offer a competitive rewards package and the opportunity to work with a world-class team.

You’ll Also Have Access To

- Staff wine allowance and access to unique wine specials 
- Paid Parental Leave

- Vinarchy Anniversary Day off 
- Go Beyond Day - making a difference in your local community 
- Access to an extensive online learning library 
- Annual Flu Vaccination Program 
- Employee Assistance Program

We design and manufacture next generation PV tracking systems that dramatically improve the economics of solar power. Applications range from distributed generation to utility-scale power plants across domestic and international markets. It is an exciting time to join Nextracker as we expand our team to meet the challenges of rapid growth in the B2B solar industry. With one of the most experienced management teams in solar, category-leading products, and a fortified technology roadmap, Nextracker is making a dramatic impact on the power plant of the future.

Summary of Role

The Business Analyst will be part of the rapidly developing Foundation Solutions business unit, working with the global Nextracker team and closely with the Foundation Solutions Director this role will assume significant strategic responsibility for the development and continual improvement of key business systems, operational processes and relationships within Nextracker and with our network of clients and partners.

Operational responsibilities will be broad and will develop with the business, a background in operational excellence will be regarded highly.

The role will require excellent written language skills to meet our knowledge sharing objectives within the Australian market and our desire to develop a training excellence program.

At Nextracker, we are leading in the energy transition, providing the most comprehensive portfolio of intelligent solar tracker and software solutions for solar power plants, as well as strategic services to capture the full value of solar power plants for our customers. For us at Nextracker, sustainability is not just a word. It's a core part of our business, values and our operations. Associate Customer Security Operations Center (CSOC) Analyst (Native-Japanese-speaking) - Melbourne, Australia

Leveraging our growing security product suite, an Associate CSOC Analyst contributes real world security insights to Fastly and our customers as part of our Customer Security Operations Center (CSOC) team, as we address Internet-scale threats.

The CSOC team provides operational support for Fastly’s security products and services. Associate Analysts within this team focus on delivering outstanding security product services to our customers. The team works with the security, operations, and customer organizations internally to respond to security threats faced on the Internet today.

What You'll Do

You will be responsible for providing product support for Fastly's security products, including our Next-Gen WAF, to customers across the globe. This includes assisting with product installation, configuration, troubleshooting, and triage of security incidents. You will help customers establish and secure their web applications, debug WAF deployment configurations, and resolve technical issues to ensure they derive maximum benefit from Fastly's security offerings. Your fluent Japanese language skills will be utilized to support our Japanese-speaking customers. Associate Analysts are responsible for the following:

- Manage incoming customer inquiries
- Deliver exceptional support for customer security concerns
- Ensure high-quality customer interactions
- Conduct thorough troubleshooting and triage of customer-reported issues related to WAF and other security product functionalities
- Document common issues, solutions, and best practices to contribute to internal knowledge bases and runbooks
- Address inquiries and alerts in accordance with established Service Level Agreements (SLAs)
- Contribute to the development of scalable organizational processes and policies
- Escalate complex issues to senior team members as required

What We're Looking For

- Native Japanese and fluency in English (essential)
- Strong interest in infosec and application security
- A foundational understanding of common web application vulnerabilities (e.g., OWASP Top 10)
- Working knowledge of core internet technologies like DNS, HTTP, and TLS
- Some experience with command line Linux server environments (Windows Server a plus)
- An understanding of the OSI model
- 1+ years of experience in a technical support, DevOps, or Solutions Engineering role, ideally focused on application security, web infrastructure, or cloud environments
- Familiarity with configuring, deploying, or managing applications in cloud environments (e.g., AWS, Azure, GCP) or using CI/CD pipelines is a plus
- Practical troubleshooting experience with WAF products, network proxies, or application delivery controllers
- Scripting ability in popular coding/scripting languages
- Desire to contribute to the processes and policies that scale our organization as we grow
- Self-motivated and able to work independently, but also thrives in a supportive team environment
- Fluency in English (both spoken and written) required, and you know how to adapt content for different audiences
- Communicate with clients to resolve concerns and escalations; monitor and manage service-impacting issues through resolution to ensure client satisfaction
- Focused on delivering exceptional customer experiences

Work Hours

Wednesday to Sunday each week around core business hours: 9am - 6pm

Work Location(s) & Travel Requirements: 

This position is remote, but you must reside within a reasonable commuting distance of Melbourne, Australia

This position will require travel as required by your role or requested by your manager

Benefits

We care about you. Fastly works hard to create a positive environment for our employees, and we think your life outside of work is important too. We support our teams with great benefits that start on the first day of your employment with Fastly. Curious about our offerings?

Why Fastly?

- We have a huge impact. Fastly is a small company with a big reach. Not only do our customers have a tremendous user base, but we also support a growing number of open source projects and initiatives. Outside of code, employees are encouraged to share causes close to their heart with others so we can help lend a supportive hand.

As a new hire, you will be able to attend our IN-PERSON new hire orientation in our San Francisco office! It is an exciting week-long experience that we offer to new employees to build connections with colleagues across Fastly, participate in hands-on learning opportunities, and immerse yourself in our culture firsthand. 
- We value diversity. Growing and maintaining our inclusive and diverse team matters to us. We are committed to being a company where our employees feel comfortable bringing their authentic selves to work and have the ability to be successful -- every day. 
- We are passionate. Fastly is chock full of passionate people and we’re not ‘one size fits all’. Fastly employs authors, pilots, skiers, parents (of humans and animals), makeup geeks, coffee connoisseurs, and more. We love employees for who they are and what they are passionate about. 

We’re always looking for humble, sharp, and creative folks to join the Fastly team. If you think you might be a fit please apply! A fully completed application and resume or CV are required when applying.

Brief Description

Purpose of the Role:

As our new Fraud Performance Analyst, you will play a key role in protecting our business and customers by monitoring fraud trends, assessing control effectiveness and driving improvements in fraud detection strategies. Alongside a strong analytical and reporting focus, the Fraud Performance Analyst will work closely with the Fraud function to optimise and scale detection methodologies, reporting and controls.

You Will

- Develop & continuously monitor the performance of new and existing rules-based typologies and detection models to support fraud detection objectives 
- Proactively provide timely and data driven analysis and insights to better support and inform business understanding and decisions and provide recommendations of corrective actions to address business challenges 
- In conjunction with Data & Analytics teams, produce and monitor performance and operational reporting to inform decision making
- Ensure typology analysis supports compliance with relevant legislation and regulatory expectations (GICOP) 
- Support the team in pursuing and developing new business initiatives, including defining, modelling and tracking of business case benefits and identify & provide insight into drivers of cost, productivity, trends and claims leakage 
- Support the Leadership team to define and track initiative benefits aligned with the strategic direction

About the Role: 

We are seeking a skilled and motivated Data Analyst (official title: Research Associate) to join the Justice Health Group. This is a two-year full-time (1.0 FTE) appointment, suitable for someone with strong technical skills in quantitative data management and analysis, and a commitment to improving the health of marginalised populations.

This role is ideally suited to someone who thrives in a collaborative research environment, can manage complex data management and analysis tasks with limited supervision, and is passionate about producing research that supports social justice and health equity.

Your responsibilities will include, but are not limited to:

- Data Cleaning and Management
- Undertaking cleaning and manipulation of large, linked administrative datasets.
- Creating and maintaining detailed documentation, codebooks and data dictionaries.
- Data Analysis and Interpretation
- Contributing to the design and planning of data analyses, in collaboration with project leads and team members.
- Conducting appropriate statistical analyses for academic publications and other research outputs.
- Generating clean, well-documented analytic output (e.g., tables, figures, models) for use in academic and policy contexts.
- Assisting team members in the interpretation of statistical output and communicating findings to non-technical audiences.
- Collaboration and Research Support
- Working closely with research staff, students, and external collaborators across projects.
- Supporting the implementation of research protocols related to data access, cleaning, security, and governance.
- Maintaining high standards of data security, confidentiality, and ethical research practice.

Who we are looking for:

- Tertiary qualifications in a relevant quantitative discipline (e.g. public health, psychology, statistics, economics or quantitative criminology) with relevant experience and/or an equivalent combination of relevant quantitative experience and/or education/training.
- Demonstrated proficiency in quantitative analysis, statistics and/or mathematical modelling.
- Experience with time-to-event analysis methods (e.g. Cox regression).
- Demonstrated proficiency in at least one widely used statistical software package (SAS, Stata, R, or SPSS are preferred) .
- Demonstrated interest in improving health outcomes for marginalised populations, such as people with experience of incarceration.
- Demonstrated experience in using software tools for data interrogation, extraction, presentation, management and analysis of large datasets.
- Well-developed verbal and written communication skills with the ability to translate complex data into written form, which can be understood by a variety of audiences.
- Proven ability to organise time and work activities according to priorities and to meet deadlines.
- Demonstrated ability to work both independently and collaboratively as part of a team.

Desirable

- Postgraduate training in a relevant discipline (e.g. public health, psychology, statistics, economics, or quantitative criminology).
- Working knowledge of the Australian criminal justice system.
- Prior experience working with large, linked administrative datasets, especially in the health, justice, or social service domains.
- Demonstrated ability to work with data across disciplines.
- Familiarity with complex statistical methods, including survival analysis, generalised linear models, and multilevel modelling.
- Experience working in a research environment, including contributing to academic publications, technical reports, or policy briefs.

Your New Team: The Justice Health Group

The Justice Health Group is a multidisciplinary and mixed-methods research team working to improve health and wellbeing outcomes for people who come into contact with the criminal justice system, in Australia and internationally. A cornerstone of our work is the use of large-scale, cross-sectoral, linked administrative data to generate high-quality evidence, and use that evidence to advocate for meaningful change to policy, practice, and/or service design.

Our projects span youth and adult criminal justice settings, in both custodial and community contexts. We work collaboratively with government agencies, service providers, academics, Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander organisations, and people with lived experience of incarceration to ensure that our work is rigorous, ethical, and achieves real-world impact.

We work across all Australian jurisdictions, with teams based in Perth and Melbourne. We are increasingly contributing to international research and policy initiatives, including in collaboration with leading academic institutions (e.g., Yale, UBC, Oxford) and key multilateral organisations (e.g., WHO, UNICEF, ICRC).

Job summary
The Customer Authentication department is responsible for conducting due diligence on customers applying for SSL and Code Signing digital certificates to secure websites and applications.  Due to the critical nature of the business, we provide 24x7 support in a follow the sun arrangement. The Melbourne team primarily supports Asia Pacific but assists customers from all regions.  In this environment teamwork and collaboration is important to our success.
 
What you will do
To work in CAS in DigiCert, you are required to pass an extended background check, which will be carried out throughout your tenure in the company, to ensure you maintain our required trusted employee status. 
The Customer Service Specialist has two key areas of responsibility: customer authentication and customer service.  

- Customer Authentication 

- Review applications for digital certificates and decide if an applicant is eligible to receive the certificate by evaluating information on the organization.  This is achieved by following policy guidelines, and showing due diligence and care while reviewing documentation and customer information

- Determine if customer's company is a legitimate legal business entity

- Determine if customer's company has the legal right to use the internet domain name listed on the certificate signing request

- Verify that a customer's named contacts are employed at customer's company and/or have the legal right to request and/or administer the digital certificate

- Utilize local knowledge of your supported country to mitigate risk while evaluating enrolments

- Flag any suspicious applications with management

- Failure to follow policy guidelines and due care while processing may result in a breach in security, which may result in facilitating fraudulent activity on a customers’ website, and cause damage to the DigiCert brand

- Customer Service 

- Assist customers with any queries regarding their application via chat, email and phone    

- Work with the customer to ensure their applications meets our security requirements and find solutions when problems arise that delay issuance 

- Seek assistance from management and senior team members to resolve policy, process, and system issues

- Build relationships with our customers to ensure customer loyalty

- To best assist customers develop a strong knowledge of DigiCert’s products and customer portals

Additional Responsibilities
To help enhance the team’s operational effectiveness and customer satisfaction, the team is encouraged to:  

- Participate in projects and system implementations

- Continually look for ways to improve our operational effectiveness, including researching databases to assist us verify information

- Be the voice of the customer and raise issues which impact customer satisfaction

- Assist with mentoring new team members

- Share your knowledge with the team

 
What you will have

- Fluent in English and Korean

- Excellent written and oral communication in native language and any language listed on CV (including English) 

- Customer service experience

- Diploma or bachelor’s degree desirable, but not required

- Experience in a policy / compliance role an advantage (banking, finance, fraud etc.)

 
Nice to have

- Detail orientated and high level of accuracy 

- Strong PC skills and fast typing speed

- Ability to multitask

- Fast learner who is keen to continue learning and developing

- Good interpersonal skills

- Open to receiving and giving constructive feedback

- Strong decision making, and problem-solving skills is required

- Open to change – ability to work in a fast paced, changing environment

- Ability to perform under pressure to meet deadlines and targets

- Ability to work as part of a team, but also as a sole contributor within a team structure

Overview

Commencing February or March 2026

As an Equity or Macro Analyst on Susquehanna's Research team, you will partner with senior analysts and traders to identify investment opportunities. Our research analysts provide in-depth country and sector-level analysis and deliver timely insights as new information emerges throughout the trading day. This role will commence in February or March 2026, offering you the opportunity to contribute to a dynamic, collaborative, and market-driven environment.

You will be responsible for uncovering opportunities that others may overlook—either by discovering new information or reframing existing knowledge from a different perspective. This role combines quantitative finance with creative problem solving to generate trade ideas in a fast-paced proprietary trading environment.

At Susquehanna, we place a strong emphasis on education and development. You will learn directly from research analysts and traders on your desk while also participating in structured classroom education, including options theory and the decision-making strategies that underpin our trading approach.

What You’ll Do

-  Identify and analyse investment opportunities in the equity and options markets 
-  Identify and analyse catalyst events and provide opinions on the possible impacts to the market, for the stocks or sector under coverage 
-  Provide real-time opinions on breaking news 
-  Collaborate with derivative traders on investment ideas 
-  Perform stock valuation analysis and f orecast dividends 
-  Evaluate special situations such as mergers and acquisitions and other corporate actions 
-  Travel to company events and conferences as required 

What We're Looking For

-  Experience: Minimum of 2 years of relevant professional Equity/Macro or Investment Research experience 
-  Familiarity with a trading environment and derivative products preferred 
-  Working knowledge of all major asset classes (e.g. fixed income, equities, commodities, forex) beneficial but not required 
-  Prior exposure to fundamental company research preferred 
-  Degree in Finance, Economics or related discipline, distinction average WAM. 
-  Market Enthusiasts: Keeping up to date on current events and breaking news that affect the markets is something you naturally enjoy. 
-  From company/sector specific news to macro stories, you are up to date on recent headlines. 
-  Effective Communicators: You enjoy building relationships with those you work closely with. You enjoy sharing ideas and expressing your thoughts based on your own research whilst combining the expert’s opinion to come to the best trading decisions – excellent verbal and written communication skills are a must for this role! 
-  You possess strong written, analytical, and financial research skills 
-  Analytical + Logical: When it comes to decision making, you use clear and sound reasoning. 
-  You’re rational and like to use analytical data and financial research skills to come up with sensible solutions. 
-  You are a natural problem solver, you enjoy solving puzzles and love it when you discover a solution to a difficult problem, with a demonstrated interest in strategic games and/or competitive activities. 
-  Curious: You’re excited by a career in the financial markets and the reasons why markets move in the way they do. 
-  You're a self-starter, a quick learner, an effective communicator, and resourceful in solving problems 
-  You thrive in a fast-paced, dynamic environment with the ability to prioritise and multi-task 

What We Offer

-  Education: Susquehanna’s in-house education programme is widely recognised as being the best in the industry. You will attend seminars during your onboarding to learn about options and the decision-making strategies that our traders employ. You will also work with a mentor from the Equity Research team to guide you along the way. 
-  Decision Making: Using game theory, decision science, poker, and other strategy games. It’s true what you’ve heard! 
-  Real Impact: You will work collaboratively with research analysts and traders on your desk to develop trade ideas on your allocated basket of stocks and provide real-time opinions on breaking news throughout the trading day. 
-  Culture: Our culture allows employees of every level to thrive. We are not your typical trading firm – the environment is casual, collaborative and we focus on continuous development, no matter how long you’ve been in Susquehanna. 
-  Perks: Based in Sydney, on the top two floors of Tower 1 in Barangaroo, our space provides beautiful harbor views of the Opera House and Harbour Bridge. To name a few of our favourite perks, our employees make the most of our free onsite catering, game room, and social events (company-wide parties, poker tournaments, and Friday night socials).

-  Online Assessment (Finance knowledge and quantitative skills)
-  Phone Interview (Recruiter)

If successful, the remaining activities will commence from January 2026

-  Case Study (Simulated project based on daily duties)
-  Virtual Interview (Case study review and quantitative assessment)
-  Office Interview (Analyst interview, trade floor visit, and office tour)
